§ 3. Possessing so many claims upon our attention, it is much to be regretted that the manuscript from which the work is here printed is not only imperfect but incor- rect. Several portione have been lost since the Durham copy was transcribed, and others have become so defaced by time, by constant use, and by damp, as to be now ille- gible ; while the text which does remain is so incorrectly written as in many passages to be unintelligible. Nor do the defects and errors here mentioned admit of an easy remedy‚ for, although many of the component parts are exactly similar to the corresponding passages in the Sacramentary of Pope Gregory the Great,¹ no other copy of the work, as a whole, is known to be in existence.
